# Architecture Rules

## Two-Track Engine (Mandatory Separation)

- Track 1: deterministic calculation engine
  - Location: `src/lib/calculators/`
  - Must be pure TypeScript functions (input -> output).
  - No DB/API side effects, no LLM-based numeric calculation.
  - Include (extend as implemented): `calculateSuneungScore`, `calculateSusiGPA`, `calculateZScore`, `calculateAdmissionProbability`, `checkSuneungMinimum`, `checkSubjectEligibility`, `analyzeSubjectAdvantage`, `calcSuneungMinimumProbability`, `detectGibupGap`, `calcDDay`, `calcSuneungNapchiRisk`.
- Track 2: RAG/LLM intelligence engine
  - Location: `src/app/api/chat/`
  - Uses retrieval + Claude; when numeric logic is required, call Track 1 functions as tools.

## Data Model Baseline

- Core tables include:
  - `students`
  - `academic_records`
  - `student_records_text`
  - `university_scoring_rules`
  - `susi_gpa_rules`
  - `converted_standard_scores`
  - `guideline_chunks`
  - `admission_schedules`
  - `subject_profiles` (P1-11, per-student CSAT elective profile)
  - `univ_subject_requirements` (P1-11, per-university/dept rules; plus `universities`, `departments` FKs)

## Access Control

- RLS applies to all tables.
- User-owned data tables must enforce `auth.uid()` scope (e.g., `id` or `student_id`).
- Shared reference tables are read-only for authenticated users.
